{"id":16291,"date":"2023-10-05T04:51:26","date_gmt":"2023-10-05T04:51:26","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/?page_id=16291"},"modified":"2023-10-06T02:51:59","modified_gmt":"2023-10-06T02:51:59","slug":"development-milestones-adolescent-years","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/development-milestones-adolescent-years\/","title":{"rendered":"Development Milestones &#8211; Adolescent Years"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>[vc_row full_width=&#8221;stretch_row_content&#8221; equal_height=&#8221;yes&#8221; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1696483575331{margin-top: -10px !important;margin-bottom: 10px !important;padding-right: 100px !important;padding-left: 100px !important;background-image: url(https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/10\/joyful-multiethnic-friends-taking-funny-group-selfie-scaled.jpg?id=16309) !important;background-position: center !important;background-repeat: no-repeat !important;background-size: cover !important;}&#8221;][vc_column width=&#8221;2\/3&#8243;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1696485206827{margin-top: 120px !important;margin-bottom: 45px !important;padding-top: 20px !important;padding-right: 20px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;padding-left: 20px !important;background-color: rgba(0,0,0,0.48) !important;*background-color: rgb(0,0,0) !important;}&#8221;]<span style=\"color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"font-size: 40px;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: Antonio;\">D<\/span><\/strong><\/span><span style=\"font-size: 40px;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: Antonio;\">evelopment Milestones \u2502 Adolescent Years<br \/>\n<\/span><\/strong><\/span><\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; color: #ffffff;\">This period signifies substantial changes in a teenager&#8217;s cognitive, emotional, and social development, as well as physical maturation. Teens are crafting their individuality and beliefs, with friendships remaining vital. Simultaneously, they&#8217;re gaining a clearer self-identity and growing interests. This phase also marks preparation for greater independence and responsibility, often involving part-time work and preparations for leaving home post-high school.<\/span>[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><div class=\"notranslate side-menu is-hidden is-right -center has-shadow\" id=\"side-menu-2\"><ul class=\"sm-list\"><li class=\"sm-item\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/benefits-of-aba-therapy\/\"  class=\"sm-link\" target=\"_self\"><span class=\"sm-icon\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/10\/Benefits-of-ABA.svg\" alt=\"\"><\/span><span class=\"sm-label\">Benefits of ABA Therapy<\/span><\/a><\/li><li class=\"sm-item\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/autism-101\/\"  class=\"sm-link\" target=\"_self\"><span class=\"sm-icon\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/10\/Autism-101.svg\" alt=\"\"><\/span><span class=\"sm-label\">Autism 101<\/span><\/a><\/li><li class=\"sm-item\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/attention-deficit-hyperactivity-disorder-adhd\/\"  class=\"sm-link\" target=\"_self\"><span class=\"sm-icon\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/10\/ADHD.svg\" alt=\"\"><\/span><span class=\"sm-label\">ADHD<\/span><\/a><\/li><li class=\"sm-item\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/developmental-disorders\/\"  class=\"sm-link\" target=\"_self\"><span class=\"sm-icon\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/10\/Development-Disorders.svg\" alt=\"\"><\/span><span class=\"sm-label\">Development Disorders<\/span><\/a><\/li><li class=\"sm-item\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/parent-family-coaching\/\"  class=\"sm-link\" target=\"_self\"><span class=\"sm-icon\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Parent-Family-Coaching.svg\" alt=\"\"><\/span><span class=\"sm-label\">Parent &amp; Family Coaching<\/span><\/a><\/li><li class=\"sm-item\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/aba-assessment\/\"  class=\"sm-link\" target=\"_self\"><span class=\"sm-icon\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Assessment.svg\" alt=\"\"><\/span><span class=\"sm-label\">ABA Assessment<\/span><\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/div>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][vc_column width=&#8221;1\/3&#8243;][vc_empty_space height=&#8221;300px&#8221;][vc_column_text css_animation=&#8221;rollIn&#8221; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1696485239449{padding-top: 50px !important;padding-right: 40px !important;}&#8221;]<img decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-15776 alignright\" src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Orange-Dots.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"100\" height=\"95\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Orange-Dots.png 304w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Orange-Dots-300x286.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 100px) 100vw, 100px\" \/>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row full_width=&#8221;stretch_row_content&#8221; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1696485256990{margin-top: 40px !important;padding-right: 100px !important;padding-left: 100px !important;}&#8221;][vc_column][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1694980556693{padding-right: 80px !important;padding-left: 80px !important;}&#8221;]<span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; font-size: 22px; color: #404040;\">There are<span style=\"color: #f3781e;\"><strong> three broad stages of development<\/strong><\/span>: early childhood, middle childhood, and adolescence organized around the <span style=\"color: #f3781e;\"><strong>five primary skills of development in each stage<\/strong><\/span>: cognitive, physical, social and emotional, language and communication, and adaptive. <span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\">The boundaries of each developmental stage are not rigidly fixed. Every child is unique, and as a result, each child or young adult will have their own distinct learning and behavioral patterns, along with individual challenges that may necessitate attention and intervention. These developmental milestones serve as general guidelines, but they may not necessarily signify the presence of a problem.<\/span><\/span>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row full_width=&#8221;stretch_row_content&#8221; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1695053727132{margin-top: 50px !important;padding-right: 80px !important;padding-left: 80px !important;}&#8221;][vc_column][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;1\/5&#8243;][vc_column_text css_animation=&#8221;rollIn&#8221; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1695053754556{padding-right: 60px !important;padding-left: 60px !important;}&#8221;]<img decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-full wp-image-15618 aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/DM-Icon-5B.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"280\" height=\"280\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/DM-Icon-5B.png 280w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/DM-Icon-5B-150x150.png 150w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/DM-Icon-5B-100x100.png 100w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/DM-Icon-5B-120x120.png 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 280px) 100vw, 280px\" \/>[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1694979951967{padding-right: 30px !important;padding-left: 30px !important;}&#8221;]<span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\"><span style=\"font-size: 13pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Antonio; font-size: 18px; color: #333333;\"><strong>Physical Skills<\/strong><\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-size: 12pt; color: #404040;\">Physical development includes growth and functionality of muscles and body parts. Gross motor skills involve the large muscles in the arms, legs and torso.\u00a0<\/span><\/span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; color: #404040;\">Fine motor skills involve the movement and use of hands and upper extremities.<\/span><\/span>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;1\/5&#8243;][vc_column_text css_animation=&#8221;rollIn&#8221; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1695053791787{padding-right: 60px !important;padding-left: 60px !important;}&#8221;]<img decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-15615 size-full aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/DM-Icon-2B.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"281\" height=\"280\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/DM-Icon-2B.png 281w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/DM-Icon-2B-150x150.png 150w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/DM-Icon-2B-100x100.png 100w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/DM-Icon-2B-120x120.png 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 281px) 100vw, 281px\" \/>[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1694980577016{padding-right: 30px !important;padding-left: 30px !important;}&#8221;]<span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; font-size: 13pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Antonio; font-size: 18px; color: #333333;\"><strong>Cognitive Skills<\/strong><\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-size: 12pt; color: #404040;\">Cognitive development is critical to a child\u2019s growth. It describes how a child\u2019s brain\u00a0 develops, and includes skills such as thinking, learning, exploring and problem solving. It also affects other areas of a child\u2019s development, including language and social skills.<\/span><\/span>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;1\/5&#8243;][vc_column_text css_animation=&#8221;rollIn&#8221; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1695053800404{padding-right: 60px !important;padding-left: 60px !important;}&#8221;]<img decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-full wp-image-15616 aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/DM-Icon-3B.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"280\" height=\"280\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/DM-Icon-3B.png 280w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/DM-Icon-3B-150x150.png 150w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/DM-Icon-3B-100x100.png 100w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/DM-Icon-3B-120x120.png 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 280px) 100vw, 280px\" \/>[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1694980585115{padding-right: 20px !important;padding-left: 30px !important;}&#8221;]<span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; font-size: 13pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Antonio; font-size: 18px; color: #333333;\"><strong>Language Skills<\/strong><\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-size: 12pt; color: #404040;\">Language development milestones measure the child\u2019s receptive (hearing and understanding) and expressive (speech) abilities. Language development starts with sounds and gestures, then words and sentences.<\/span><\/span>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;1\/5&#8243;][vc_column_text css_animation=&#8221;rollIn&#8221; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1695053806885{padding-right: 60px !important;padding-left: 60px !important;}&#8221;]<img decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-full wp-image-15619 aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/DM-Icon-1B.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"281\" height=\"280\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/DM-Icon-1B.png 281w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/DM-Icon-1B-150x150.png 150w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/DM-Icon-1B-100x100.png 100w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/DM-Icon-1B-120x120.png 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 281px) 100vw, 281px\" \/>[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1694895424843{padding-right: 30px !important;padding-left: 30px !important;}&#8221;]<span style=\"font-family: Antonio; font-size: 18px; color: #333333;\"><strong>Social\/Emotional Skills<\/strong><\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; font-size: 12pt; color: #404040;\">Social and emotional development focuses on a child\u2019s ability to express emotions effectively, follow rules and directions, form positive relationships with others, and build confidence.<\/span>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;1\/5&#8243;][vc_column_text css_animation=&#8221;rollIn&#8221; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1695053813641{padding-right: 60px !important;padding-left: 60px !important;}&#8221;]<img decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-full wp-image-15617 aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/DM-Icon-4B.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"280\" height=\"280\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/DM-Icon-4B.png 280w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/DM-Icon-4B-150x150.png 150w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/DM-Icon-4B-100x100.png 100w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/DM-Icon-4B-120x120.png 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 280px) 100vw, 280px\" \/>[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text]<span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; font-size: 13pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: Antonio; font-size: 18px; color: #333333;\">Adaptive Developmental Skills<\/span><br \/>\n<\/strong><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><span style=\"color: #404040;\">Referring to age-appropriate life skills, <strong><span style=\"color: #f3781e;\">\r\n\t<a class=\"paoc-popup-click paoc-popup-cust-8282 paoc-popup-simple_link paoc-popup-link\" href=\"javascript:void(0);\">\"adaptive and self-care skills\"<\/a>\r\n\r\n<\/span><\/strong> focus on the ability for the child to learn self-help skills and self-sufficiency skills so they can live independent and productive lives as adolescents and adults.<\/span>\u00a0<\/span><\/span>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column_inner][\/vc_row_inner][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row full_width=&#8221;stretch_row_content&#8221; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1695183302820{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-right: 80px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;padding-left: 80px !important;}&#8221;][vc_column][vc_separator style=&#8221;dashed&#8221; border_width=&#8221;3&#8243; el_width=&#8221;50&#8243;][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row full_width=&#8221;stretch_row_content&#8221; content_placement=&#8221;middle&#8221; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1696525132912{margin-right: 80px !important;margin-left: 80px !important;background-color: #eee4ce !important;}&#8221;][vc_column width=&#8221;1\/4&#8243;][vc_column_text]<img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-15345\" src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/2558328a.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"580\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/2558328a.png 750w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/2558328a-300x232.png 300w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/2558328a-500x387.png 500w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\" \/>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][vc_column width=&#8221;3\/4&#8243;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1696483937775{margin-right: 50px !important;padding-top: 20px !important;padding-right: 20px !important;padding-left: 20px !important;}&#8221;]<span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\"><span style=\"color: #00b3e6; font-family: 'DM Serif Display'; font-size: 31px;\"><em><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><span style=\"color: #f3781e;\">Adolescence (12-18 Years+)<br \/>\n<\/span><\/span><\/em><\/span><\/span><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; font-size: 16px; color: #404040;\">Adolescence signals diverse, confusing, even frightening changes due to significant physical, emotional and cognitive growth, new situations, responsibilities, and people. \u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; font-size: 16px; color: #404040;\">Frequent mood swings, episodes of depression, and other psychological challenges are not uncommon. While these shifts are often attributed to hormonal changes, it&#8217;s crucial to recognize that your child will grapple with various challenges and confrontations, leading to fluctuating and inconsistent behaviors that tend to stabilize with time and maturity.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; font-size: 16px; color: #404040;\">As adolescents transition toward adulthood, they experience a compelling desire for greater independence from their families. Cognitively, they gain the capacity to address more abstract and hypothetical problems, representing a significant stride toward emotional autonomy. This shift involves a notable transformation in their modes of thought and reasoning, often leading adolescents to rely more on their peers for guidance and emotional support, as opposed to their families.<\/span>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row full_width=&#8221;stretch_row_content&#8221; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1695231085064{margin-top: -50px !important;padding-right: 100px !important;padding-left: 100px !important;}&#8221;][vc_column width=&#8221;1\/3&#8243;][\/vc_column][vc_column width=&#8221;1\/3&#8243;][\/vc_column][vc_column width=&#8221;1\/3&#8243;][vc_column_text css_animation=&#8221;rollIn&#8221; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1696484773104{margin-top: -70px !important;padding-right: 40px !important;}&#8221;]<img decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-15517 alignright\" src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Graphic-Circles.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"111\" height=\"131\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Graphic-Circles.png 464w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/Graphic-Circles-254x300.png 254w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 111px) 100vw, 111px\" \/>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row full_width=&#8221;stretch_row_content&#8221; gap=&#8221;15&#8243; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1696484801327{margin-top: 25px !important;padding-right: 80px !important;padding-left: 80px !important;}&#8221;][vc_column width=&#8221;1\/3&#8243;][vc_single_image image=&#8221;15479&#8243; img_size=&#8221;full&#8221; style=&#8221;vc_box_shadow_3d&#8221;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1696560677575{padding-right: 20px !important;padding-left: 20px !important;}&#8221;]<span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; font-size: 15px; color: #404040;\"><span style=\"font-family: 'DM Serif Display'; font-size: 20px; color: #404040;\">12-14 Years<br \/>\n<\/span><\/span><span style=\"font-size: 15px; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\">Often referred to as early adolescence, your child grows taller and stronger and also starts to feel and think in more mature ways, signaling the roots of a transition to adulthood.\u00a0\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; font-size: 15px; color: #404040;\">This is a time of many physical, mental, emotional, and social changes. Puberty begins. Hormones activate. \r\n\t<a class=\"paoc-popup-click paoc-popup-cust-16360 paoc-popup-simple_link paoc-popup-link\" href=\"javascript:void(0);\">Most boys begin to grow facial and pubic hair, and their voices deepen.<\/a>\r\n\r\n \r\n\t<a class=\"paoc-popup-click paoc-popup-cust-16357 paoc-popup-simple_link paoc-popup-link\" href=\"javascript:void(0);\">Most girls begin to grow pubic hair as well as breasts and start their periods.<\/a>\r\n\r\n Early adolescents often worry about these myriad changes and how they are now viewed by others. <\/span><\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-15549 aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/3-dots.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"65\" height=\"24\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/3-dots.png 473w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/3-dots-300x110.png 300w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/3-dots-458x174.png 458w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 65px) 100vw, 65px\" \/>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][vc_column width=&#8221;2\/3&#8243;][vc_column_text]<style id=\"sp_tab_dynamic_style7464\">#sp-tabpro-wrapper_7464.sp-tab__lay-default .sp-tab__tab-content {width: 100%;}#sp-tabpro-wrapper_7464 .animated {-webkit-animation-duration: 500ms;animation-duration: 500ms;}#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464 .sp-tab__nav {justify-content: start;}#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464.sp-tab__lay-default.sp-tab__horizontal-bottom {display: flex;flex-direction: column-reverse;}#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464.sp-tab__lay-default.sp-tab__horizontal-bottom > ul {border-top: 1px solid #cccccc;border-bottom: 0;margin-top: 0;}#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464.sp-tab__lay-default.sp-tab__horizontal-bottom > ul > li label.sp-tab__active {border-color: transparent #cccccc#cccccc;margin-top: -1px;}#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464.sp-tab__lay-default.sp-tab__horizontal-bottom > ul > li label,#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464.sp-tab__lay-default.sp-tab__horizontal-bottom > ul > li a,#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464.sp-tab__lay-default.sp-tab__horizontal-bottom > ul > .sp-tab__nav-item {border-top: 0;border-top-left-radius: 0;border-top-right-radius: 0;border-bottom-left-radius: 2px;border-bottom-right-radius: 2px;}#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464.sp-tab__lay-default.sp-tab__horizontal-bottom > ul {border-bottom: none;}#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464.sp-tab__lay-default.sp-tab__horizontal-bottom .sp-tab__tab-content .sp-tab__tab-pane {border-top: 0px solid #cccccc;border-bottom: 0;}#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464.sp-tab__lay-default .sp-tab__tab-content .sp-tab-content > ul,#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464.sp-tab__lay-default .sp-tab__tab-content .sp-tab-content > ol {border-bottom: none;}#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464 > .sp-tab__nav-tabs .sp-tab__nav-link.sp-tab__active .sp-tab__tab_title,#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464.sp-tab__lay-default label > .sp-tab__card-header {color: #eeeeee;}#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464 > .sp-tab__nav-tabs > .sp-tab__nav-item.show .sp-tab__nav-link,#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464 > .sp-tab__nav-tabs > .sp-tab__nav-item .sp-tab__nav-link.sp-tab__active,#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464.sp-tab__lay-default label > .sp-tab__card-header {background-color: #00b3e6;}#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464 .sp-tab__nav-tabs .sp-tab__nav-item.show .sp-tab__nav-link,#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464.sp-tab__lay-default ul li label.sp-tab__active {border-color: #cccccc#cccccc transparent;}#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464.sp-tab__lay-default > ul > li > label,#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464.sp-tab__lay-default > ul > li > a {cursor: pointer;border-color: #cccccc;padding-top: 15px;padding-right: 15px;padding-bottom: 15px;padding-left: 15px;}#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464 > .sp-tab__nav-tabs .sp-tab__nav-link {border: 1px solid #cccccc;height: 100%;}#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464.sp-tab__lay-default > ul > li label,#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464.sp-tab__lay-default > ul > li a,#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464.sp-tab__lay-default > ul > .sp-tab__nav-item {border-top-left-radius: 2px;border-top-right-radius: 2px;}#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464 .sp-tab__nav-tabs .sp-tab__nav-item {margin-bottom: -1px; }#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464.sp-tab__lay-default > ul .sp-tab__nav-item,#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464.sp-tab__lay-default label.collapsed > .sp-tab__card-header {background-color: #f8f4eb;}#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464.sp-tab__lay-default > ul .sp-tab__nav-item {margin-right: 0px;margin-top: 5px;}#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464.sp-tab__lay-default > ul .sp-tab__nav-item label:hover .sp-tab__tab_title,#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464.sp-tab__lay-default > ul .sp-tab__nav-item a:hover .sp-tab__tab_title,#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464.sp-tab__lay-default label.collapsed .sp-tab__card-header:hover {color: #04b1e7;transition: .3s;}#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464.sp-tab__lay-default > ul .sp-tab__nav-item:hover,#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464.sp-tab__lay-default label.collapsed > .sp-tab__card-header:hover {background-color: #eeeeee;}#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464.sp-tab__lay-default > ul .sp-tab__nav-item:last-child {margin-right: 0;}#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464.sp-tab__lay-default > .sp-tab__tab-content .sp-tab__tab-pane {border: 0px solid #cccccc;padding-top: 20px;padding-right: 20px;padding-bottom: 20px;padding-left: 20px;border-top: 0px;background-color: #f8f4eb;}#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464.sp-tab__lay-default > ul {border-bottom: 0px solid #cccccc;}@media(max-width:500px) {#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464.sp-tab__lay-default > ul li.sp-tab__nav-item {width: 100%;margin-right: 0px;}#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464.sp-tab__lay-default > ul li.sp-tab__nav-item:last-child {margin-bottom: -1px;}}#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464.sp-tab__lay-default > ul .sp-tab__nav-item .sp-tab__tab_title,#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464.sp-tab__lay-default label > .sp-tab__card-header {font-weight: 600;font-style: normal;font-size: 16px;line-height: 22px;letter-spacing: 0px;color: #444444;margin: 0px;}#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464.sp-tab__lay-default > .sp-tab__tab-content .sp-tab__tab-pane {font-weight: 400;font-style: normal;font-size: 16px;line-height: 24px;letter-spacing: 0px;color: #000000;}#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464.sp-tab__lay-default > .sp-tab__tab-content .sp-tab__tab-pane ul li a, #sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464.sp-tab__lay-default .sp-tab__tab-content .sp-tab__tab-pane ol li a {color: #000000;}<\/style>\t\t<div id=\"sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_7464\" class=\"sp-tab__lay-default\" data-preloader=\"1\" data-activemode=\"tabs-activator-event-click\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"sp-tab__preloader\">\n\t\t<div class=\"sp-tab__spinner\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"rect1\"><\/div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"rect2\"><\/div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"rect3\"><\/div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"rect4\"><\/div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"rect5\"><\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t<\/div>\n\t<ul class=\"sp-tab__nav sp-tab__nav-tabs\" id=\"sp-tab__ul\" role=\"tablist\">\n\t\t\t\t<li class=\"sp-tab__nav-item\" role=\"tab\">\n\t\t\t\t<label class=\"sp-tab__nav-link sp-tab__active\" data-sptoggle=\"tab\" for=\"#tab-74641\" role=\"tab\" aria-controls=tab-74641 aria-selected=true tabindex=0>\n\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"tab_title_area\"><H6 class=\"sp-tab__tab_title\">Physical <\/H6><\/span>\n\t\t\t\t<\/label>\n\t\t\t<\/li>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<li class=\"sp-tab__nav-item\" role=\"tab\">\n\t\t\t\t<label class=\"sp-tab__nav-link\" data-sptoggle=\"tab\" for=\"#tab-74642\" role=\"tab\" aria-controls=tab-74642 aria-selected=true tabindex=0>\n\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"tab_title_area\"><H6 class=\"sp-tab__tab_title\">Cognitive<\/H6><\/span>\n\t\t\t\t<\/label>\n\t\t\t<\/li>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<li class=\"sp-tab__nav-item\" role=\"tab\">\n\t\t\t\t<label class=\"sp-tab__nav-link\" data-sptoggle=\"tab\" for=\"#tab-74643\" role=\"tab\" aria-controls=tab-74643 aria-selected=true tabindex=0>\n\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"tab_title_area\"><H6 class=\"sp-tab__tab_title\">Social <\/H6><\/span>\n\t\t\t\t<\/label>\n\t\t\t<\/li>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<li class=\"sp-tab__nav-item\" role=\"tab\">\n\t\t\t\t<label class=\"sp-tab__nav-link\" data-sptoggle=\"tab\" for=\"#tab-74644\" role=\"tab\" aria-controls=tab-74644 aria-selected=true tabindex=0>\n\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"tab_title_area\"><H6 class=\"sp-tab__tab_title\">Emotional <\/H6><\/span>\n\t\t\t\t<\/label>\n\t\t\t<\/li>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<li class=\"sp-tab__nav-item\" role=\"tab\">\n\t\t\t\t<label class=\"sp-tab__nav-link\" data-sptoggle=\"tab\" for=\"#tab-74645\" role=\"tab\" aria-controls=tab-74645 aria-selected=true tabindex=0>\n\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"tab_title_area\"><H6 class=\"sp-tab__tab_title\">Language<\/H6><\/span>\n\t\t\t\t<\/label>\n\t\t\t<\/li>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<li class=\"sp-tab__nav-item\" role=\"tab\">\n\t\t\t\t<label class=\"sp-tab__nav-link\" data-sptoggle=\"tab\" for=\"#tab-74646\" role=\"tab\" aria-controls=tab-74646 aria-selected=true tabindex=0>\n\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"tab_title_area\"><H6 class=\"sp-tab__tab_title\">Puberty - Boys<\/H6><\/span>\n\t\t\t\t<\/label>\n\t\t\t<\/li>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<li class=\"sp-tab__nav-item\" role=\"tab\">\n\t\t\t\t<label class=\"sp-tab__nav-link\" data-sptoggle=\"tab\" for=\"#tab-74647\" role=\"tab\" aria-controls=tab-74647 aria-selected=true tabindex=0>\n\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"tab_title_area\"><H6 class=\"sp-tab__tab_title\">Puberty - Girls<\/H6><\/span>\n\t\t\t\t<\/label>\n\t\t\t<\/li>\n\t\t\t<\/ul>\n<div class=\"sp-tab__tab-content\">\n\t\t\t\t<div id=\"tab-74641\" class=\"sp-tab__tab-pane sp-tab__show sp-tab__active\" role=\"tabpanel\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"sp-tab-content animated fadeIn\"><ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; color: #000000; font-size: 15px;\">Growth spurt begins with the accompanying growth pains and cramps, and the need to sleep and eat more.<\/span>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; color: #000000; font-size: 15px;\">Girls begin at about age 11-12.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; color: #000000; font-size: 15px;\">Boys begin at about age 13-14.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; color: #000000; font-size: 15px;\">With girls, puberty is marked by physical changes include increased body fat, beginning of breast enlargement, pubic hair growth, widening hips, underarm hair growth, oilier skin and hair, and the first menstrual period.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; color: #000000; font-size: 15px;\">With boys, puberty is marked by physical changes might include larger muscles, vocal changes, oilier hair and skin, the beginning of underarm, facial and pubic hair, darkening scrotum, and testicle and penis growth.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; color: #000000; font-size: 15px;\">Boys may lag girls in height during these years, but they usually end up taller.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; color: #000000; font-size: 15px;\">May be a little awkward or clumsy as brains need time to adjust to longer limbs and bigger bodies.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"tab-74642\" class=\"sp-tab__tab-pane \" role=\"tabpanel\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"sp-tab-content animated fadeIn\"><ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; color: #000000; font-size: 15px;\">Thinks in concrete ways but gradually begins to grasp abstract and symbolic concepts and considers\u00a0the difference between logical thinking vs. abstract thinking.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; color: #000000; font-size: 15px;\">Develops deductive reasoning abilities and demonstrates a more strategic and methodical approach to problems.\u00a0<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; color: #000000; font-size: 15px;\">Begins to see that issues are not just clear-cut, and that information can be interpreted in different ways.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; color: #000000; font-size: 15px;\">Typically focuses on the present but begins to understand things in the long-term.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; color: #000000; font-size: 15px;\">Develops a stronger sense of right and wrong.\u00a0Understands shades of gray, wrestles with abstract concepts like love or justice, and formulates values based on thinking and analyzing as opposed to only by feeling or experiencing.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; color: #000000; font-size: 15px;\">Develops better decision-making skills.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; color: #000000; font-size: 15px;\">Can initiate and carry out their own tasks without the supervision of others.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"tab-74643\" class=\"sp-tab__tab-pane \" role=\"tabpanel\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"sp-tab-content animated fadeIn\"><ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; color: #000000; font-size: 15px;\">Becomes more independent from families.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; color: #000000; font-size: 15px;\">May form strong friendships and prefer to be with their friends or on their own rather than with family members.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; color: #000000; font-size: 15px;\">May look to friends, instead of parents, for advice. Shows more interest in and influence by peer group.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; color: #000000; font-size: 15px;\">Searches for intimacy, tends to romanticize.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; color: #000000; font-size: 15px;\">Focuses on themselves; going back and forth between high expectations and lack of confidence.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"tab-74644\" class=\"sp-tab__tab-pane \" role=\"tabpanel\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"sp-tab-content animated fadeIn\"><ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; color: #000000; font-size: 15px;\">May grow sullen and aloof; loses patience with meaningless activity.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; color: #000000; font-size: 15px;\">Shows more interest in friends and less interest in family. Looks to friends, instead of parents, for advice. Shows more interest in and influence by peer group with whom they form strong and complex friendships.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; color: #000000; font-size: 15px;\">Begins to accept and enjoy their own uniqueness but still seeks approval from peer groups.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; color: #000000; font-size: 15px;\">Begins to see self from viewpoint of others; looks for confidence from others in their decisions.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; color: #000000; font-size: 15px;\">Expresses less affection toward parents; sometimes might seem rude or short-tempered.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; color: #000000; font-size: 15px;\">Focuses on themselves; going back and forth between high expectations and lack of confidence.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; color: #000000; font-size: 15px;\">Vacillates between distress and happiness which can lead to self-destructive and risky behavior tempered by questioning authority and\/or succumbing to peer pressure.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; font-size: 15px; color: #404040;\">May be self-centered and can be insensitive to others.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; font-size: 15px; color: #404040;\">Is better able to express feelings through talking.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"tab-74645\" class=\"sp-tab__tab-pane \" role=\"tabpanel\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"sp-tab-content animated fadeIn\"><ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; color: #000000; font-size: 15px;\">Begins to reason, think abstractly, and apply logic.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; color: #000000; font-size: 15px;\">Demonstrates an increased ability to look beyond literal interpretations and understands the metaphoric uses of language.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; color: #000000; font-size: 15px;\">Increases in metalinguistic awareness (the ability to think about how language is used\u2014to persuade, to correct, to endear, etc.).<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; color: #000000; font-size: 15px;\">Begins to understand how to form analogies.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; color: #000000; font-size: 15px;\">Balances complex ideas and the ability to manipulate them in their head.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; color: #000000; font-size: 15px;\">Understands the subtleties of language improving their ability to understand multiclause sentences.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; color: #000000; font-size: 15px;\">Able to comprehend proverbs and detect sarcasm.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; color: #000000; font-size: 15px;\">Grows into strong readers and uses their language and literacy skills across the subject areas in school, and as a tool in other areas of importance.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; color: #000000; font-size: 15px;\">Enjoys demonstrating acquired knowledge.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"tab-74646\" class=\"sp-tab__tab-pane \" role=\"tabpanel\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"sp-tab-content animated fadeIn\"><p><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-16361 aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/10\/Boy-in-Puberty.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"488\" height=\"345\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/10\/Boy-in-Puberty.png 3496w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/10\/Boy-in-Puberty-300x212.png 300w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/10\/Boy-in-Puberty-1024x725.png 1024w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/10\/Boy-in-Puberty-768x543.png 768w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/10\/Boy-in-Puberty-1536x1087.png 1536w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/10\/Boy-in-Puberty-2048x1449.png 2048w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/10\/Boy-in-Puberty-500x354.png 500w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/10\/Boy-in-Puberty-800x566.png 800w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/10\/Boy-in-Puberty-1280x906.png 1280w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/10\/Boy-in-Puberty-1920x1359.png 1920w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 488px) 100vw, 488px\" \/><\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"tab-74647\" class=\"sp-tab__tab-pane \" role=\"tabpanel\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"sp-tab-content animated fadeIn\"><p><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-16358 aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/10\/Girl-in-Puberty.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"387\" height=\"385\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/10\/Girl-in-Puberty.png 2547w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/10\/Girl-in-Puberty-1024x1021.png 1024w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/10\/Girl-in-Puberty-150x150.png 150w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/10\/Girl-in-Puberty-768x766.png 768w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/10\/Girl-in-Puberty-1536x1531.png 1536w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/10\/Girl-in-Puberty-2048x2042.png 2048w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/10\/Girl-in-Puberty-500x498.png 500w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/10\/Girl-in-Puberty-800x797.png 800w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/10\/Girl-in-Puberty-1280x1276.png 1280w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/10\/Girl-in-Puberty-1920x1914.png 1920w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/10\/Girl-in-Puberty-100x100.png 100w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/10\/Girl-in-Puberty-120x120.png 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 387px) 100vw, 387px\" \/><\/p>\n<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t[\/vc_column_text][vc_row_inner css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1694988622042{padding-top: 50px !important;}&#8221;][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;1\/3&#8243;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1694934973229{margin-top: -25px !important;}&#8221;]<img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-15494\" src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/istockphoto-1127103538-612x612-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"612\" height=\"612\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/istockphoto-1127103538-612x612-1.png 612w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/istockphoto-1127103538-612x612-1-300x300.png 300w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/istockphoto-1127103538-612x612-1-150x150.png 150w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/istockphoto-1127103538-612x612-1-500x500.png 500w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/istockphoto-1127103538-612x612-1-100x100.png 100w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/istockphoto-1127103538-612x612-1-120x120.png 120w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/istockphoto-1127103538-612x612-1-384x384.png 384w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 612px) 100vw, 612px\" \/>[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1696525417415{margin-top: -15px !important;padding-right: 40px !important;padding-left: 40px !important;}&#8221;]<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; font-size: 14px; color: #404040;\">Actively shows more interest in physical attractiveness (body and looks), often believing they are the center of attention making them painfully self-conscious and hyper-sensitive to comments and insults.\u00a0\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;1\/3&#8243;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1694934980285{margin-top: -25px !important;}&#8221;]<img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-8451\" src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/09\/Picture40-218x300.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"163\" height=\"225\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/09\/Picture40-218x300.png 218w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/09\/Picture40-742x1024.png 742w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/09\/Picture40-768x1059.png 768w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/09\/Picture40.png 791w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 163px) 100vw, 163px\" \/>[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1696525453849{margin-top: 45px !important;padding-right: 40px !important;padding-left: 40px !important;}&#8221;]<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; font-size: 14px;\">Adolescence often radically changes the body. Girls and boys usually begin puberty around the same time their parents did.\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;1\/3&#8243;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1694934964824{margin-top: -25px !important;}&#8221;]<img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-15497\" src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/5a39b6e9e76853.61348113151373181794791681.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"2000\" height=\"2000\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/5a39b6e9e76853.61348113151373181794791681.png 2000w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/5a39b6e9e76853.61348113151373181794791681-300x300.png 300w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/5a39b6e9e76853.61348113151373181794791681-1024x1024.png 1024w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/5a39b6e9e76853.61348113151373181794791681-150x150.png 150w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/5a39b6e9e76853.61348113151373181794791681-768x768.png 768w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/5a39b6e9e76853.61348113151373181794791681-1536x1536.png 1536w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/5a39b6e9e76853.61348113151373181794791681-500x500.png 500w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/5a39b6e9e76853.61348113151373181794791681-800x800.png 800w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/5a39b6e9e76853.61348113151373181794791681-1280x1280.png 1280w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/5a39b6e9e76853.61348113151373181794791681-1920x1920.png 1920w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/5a39b6e9e76853.61348113151373181794791681-100x100.png 100w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/5a39b6e9e76853.61348113151373181794791681-120x120.png 120w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/5a39b6e9e76853.61348113151373181794791681-384x384.png 384w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px\" \/>[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1694935398217{margin-top: -20px !important;padding-right: 40px !important;padding-left: 40px !important;}&#8221;]<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; font-size: 14px; color: #404040;\">In this age group, teens begin making more of their own choices about friends, sports, studying, and school. They become more independent, with their own personality and interests, although parents remain very important.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column_inner][\/vc_row_inner][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row full_width=&#8221;stretch_row_content&#8221; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1696483961761{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-right: 80px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;padding-left: 80px !important;}&#8221;][vc_column][vc_separator style=&#8221;dashed&#8221; border_width=&#8221;3&#8243; el_width=&#8221;50&#8243;][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row full_width=&#8221;stretch_row_content&#8221; gap=&#8221;15&#8243; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1696483992394{margin-top: 35px !important;padding-right: 80px !important;padding-left: 80px !important;}&#8221;][vc_column width=&#8221;1\/3&#8243;][vc_single_image image=&#8221;16320&#8243; img_size=&#8221;full&#8221; style=&#8221;vc_box_shadow_3d&#8221;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1695184947037{padding-right: 20px !important;padding-left: 20px !important;}&#8221;]<span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; font-size: 15px; color: #404040;\"><span style=\"font-family: 'DM Serif Display'; font-size: 20px; color: #404040;\">14-16 Years<br \/>\n<\/span><\/span><span style=\"font-size: 15px; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\">In the mid- to late-teenage years, kids start thinking not just about their own lives, but also more about how the world works. This is a pivotal age as they recognize they also are heading down a path toward adulthood.\u00a0 They are developing their unique identity, gaining independence, and likely exploring (or thinking about) romantic relationships and learning the skills they need for a successful future.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 15px; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\">During these years, teens seem grow comfortable in their own skin, eager to take on the world. They are also taking on more responsibilities, navigating high school, and gaining more independence. They may even behave like they know everything. This\u00a0attitude\u2014often mixed\u00a0with a\u00a0hint of rebellion\u2014can be par for the course. On the flip side, they may also experience academic challenges, peer pressure, risky behaviors, and show insolence and disrespect.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 15px; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\">Turning 16 is a big deal to most teens. Not only does their freedom expand with the addition of a driver&#8217;s license, but they also are becoming more cognizant of what they want to do in their future. Those who plan to attend college may be visiting universities or preparing to take the appropriate standardized tests.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-15549 aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/3-dots.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"65\" height=\"24\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/3-dots.png 473w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/3-dots-300x110.png 300w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/3-dots-458x174.png 458w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 65px) 100vw, 65px\" \/>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][vc_column width=&#8221;2\/3&#8243;][vc_column_text]<style id=\"sp_tab_dynamic_style15672\">#sp-tabpro-wrapper_15672.sp-tab__lay-default .sp-tab__tab-content {width: 100%;}#sp-tabpro-wrapper_15672 .animated {-webkit-animation-duration: 500ms;animation-duration: 500ms;}#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_15672 .sp-tab__nav {justify-content: start;}#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_15672.sp-tab__lay-default.sp-tab__horizontal-bottom {display: flex;flex-direction: column-reverse;}#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_15672.sp-tab__lay-default.sp-tab__horizontal-bottom > ul {border-top: 1px solid #cccccc;border-bottom: 0;margin-top: 0;}#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_15672.sp-tab__lay-default.sp-tab__horizontal-bottom > ul > li label.sp-tab__active {border-color: transparent #cccccc#cccccc;margin-top: -1px;}#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_15672.sp-tab__lay-default.sp-tab__horizontal-bottom > ul > li label,#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_15672.sp-tab__lay-default.sp-tab__horizontal-bottom > ul > li a,#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_15672.sp-tab__lay-default.sp-tab__ho