ds\/2023\/09\/tiktok-on-mobile-768x897-1-458x532.png 458w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 163px) 100vw, 163px\" \/>[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1695185162777{margin-top: 45px !important;padding-right: 30px !important;padding-left: 30px !important;}&#8221;]<span style=\"font-size: 14px; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\">During this period, teens are deeply embedded in their social standing. Texting and social media are often very important at this age. Most teens have the ability for complex thought and can express their thoughts and opinions verbally. Peer friendships and peer experiences become very important in their social and emotional development. They spend a lot of time talking with peers, not so much with their parents as their opinions or beliefs are sometimes different than their parent or caregiver&#8217;s beliefs.<\/span>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;1\/3&#8243;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1695186019859{margin-top: 10px !important;}&#8221;]<img decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-15693 aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/9d070194f66dfa92be1e85ee9700bb46.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"235\" height=\"176\" \/>[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1695186734095{margin-top: 70px !important;padding-right: 40px !important;padding-left: 40px !important;}&#8221;]<span style=\"font-size: 14px; color: #404040;\"><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\">Begins to reason, think abstractly, and apply logic. Begins to focus thinking on emerging role in adult society. Begins to understand how the world works and their own potential in that world.\u00a0 <\/span>Increased thoughts about more global concepts such as justice, history, and politics.\u00a0\u00a0<\/span>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column_inner][\/vc_row_inner][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row full_width=&#8221;stretch_row_content&#8221; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1696483978628{padding-top: 20px !important;padding-right: 80px !important;padding-bottom: 20px !important;padding-left: 80px !important;}&#8221;][vc_column][vc_separator style=&#8221;dashed&#8221; border_width=&#8221;3&#8243; el_width=&#8221;50&#8243;][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row full_width=&#8221;stretch_row_content&#8221; gap=&#8221;15&#8243; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1696484011994{margin-top: 35px !important;padding-right: 80px !important;padding-left: 80px !important;}&#8221;][vc_column width=&#8221;1\/3&#8243;][vc_single_image image=&#8221;15676&#8243; img_size=&#8221;full&#8221; style=&#8221;vc_box_shadow_3d&#8221;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1696483886141{padding-left: 20px !important;}&#8221;]<span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; font-size: 15px; color: #404040;\"><span style=\"font-family: 'DM Serif Display'; font-size: 20px; color: #404040;\">16-18 Years+<br \/>\n<\/span><\/span><span style=\"font-size: 15px; color: #404040;\">The latter part of adolescence marks a period of swift transformation in how teenagers think, feel, and interact with others and how their bodies grow.\u00a0 By this phase, your young adult <\/span><span style=\"font-size: 15px;\">has finished puberty and grown accustomed to his or her new adult body. Most girls will be physically mature by now, having completed puberty. Boys, however, may still be maturing physically during this time.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 15px; color: #404040;\">Now, they start to assert their independence, nurture their distinctive personalities and viewpoints, discover their individual identity, and cultivate a more defined sense of self.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-15549 aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/3-dots.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"74\" height=\"27\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/3-dots.png 473w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/3-dots-300x110.png 300w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/09\/3-dots-458x174.png 458w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 74px) 100vw, 74px\" \/>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column][vc_column width=&#8221;2\/3&#8243;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1632888245336{padding-left: 80px !important;}&#8221;]<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><style id=\"sp_tab_dynamic_style8279\">#sp-tabpro-wrapper_8279.sp-tab__lay-default .sp-tab__tab-content {width: 100%;}#sp-tabpro-wrapper_8279 .animated {-webkit-animation-duration: 500ms;animation-duration: 500ms;}#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_8279 .sp-tab__nav {justify-content: start;}#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_8279.sp-tab__lay-default.sp-tab__horizontal-bottom {display: flex;flex-direction: column-reverse;}#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_8279.sp-tab__lay-default.sp-tab__horizontal-bottom > ul {border-top: 1px solid #cccccc;border-bottom: 0;margin-top: 0;}#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_8279.sp-tab__lay-default.sp-tab__horizontal-bottom > ul > li label.sp-tab__active {border-color: transparent #cccccc#cccccc;margin-top: -1px;}#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_8279.sp-tab__lay-default.sp-tab__horizontal-bottom > ul > li label,#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_8279.sp-tab__lay-default.sp-tab__horizontal-bottom > ul > li a,#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_8279.sp-tab__lay-default.sp-tab__horizontal-bottom > ul > .sp-tab__nav-item {border-top: 0;border-top-left-radius: 0;border-top-right-radius: 0;border-bottom-left-radius: 2px;border-bottom-right-radius: 2px;}#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_8279.sp-tab__lay-default.sp-tab__horizontal-bottom > ul {border-bottom: none;}#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_8279.sp-tab__lay-default.sp-tab__horizontal-bottom .sp-tab__tab-content .sp-tab__tab-pane {border-top: 0px solid #cccccc;border-bottom: 0;}#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_8279.sp-tab__lay-default .sp-tab__tab-content .sp-tab-content > ul,#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_8279.sp-tab__lay-default .sp-tab__tab-content .sp-tab-content > ol {border-bottom: none;}#sp-wp-tabs-wrapper_8279 > .sp-tab__nav-tabs .sp-tab__nav-link.sp-tab__active .sp-tab__tab_title,#sp-wp-